  "text": "All four key Activity lifecycle files were found in the local repo. (1) `Activity.java` (line 763) defines `public class Activity extends ContextThemeWrapper` with lifecycle callbacks `onCreate` (line 1818), `onStart` (line 2105), `onResume` (line 2183), `onPause` (line 2613), `onStop` (line 2842), and `onDestroy` (line 2886). (2) `ActivityThread.java` (line 296) defines `public final class ActivityThread extends ClientTransactionHandler`, which is the main thread driving lifecycle transitions on the app side. (3) `ActivityRecord.java` (line 410) defines `final class ActivityRecord extends WindowToken` \u2014 the server-side representation of an activity in the window manager. (4) `ActivityTaskManagerService.java` (line 324) defines `public class ActivityTaskManagerService extends IActivityTaskManager.Stub` \u2014 the system service managing activity stacks and tasks. The dependency chain flows from the system service (ActivityTaskManagerService) through the server-side record (ActivityRecord) to the client-side thread (ActivityThread) which ultimately invokes lifecycle methods on the Activity.",
